[Matthijs Altena, the IT-specialist who came to Hos
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Matthijs Altena, the IT-specialist who came to Hospital San Miguel twice, first to install the IT-network and then to do maintenance, is now taking another big step: he is going to run a full marathon to contribute to the running costs. Next Saturday he will try to run a full marathon in four hours, a time that many patients even need to arrive at our hospital. Matthijs contributes to the running costs, let's support Matthijs by running! #quinacare #running4runningcosts #it #putumayo #voluntering" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DJzPe1GIR4i/)

[Yesterday was the book and plant market in Nootdor
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Yesterday was the book and plant market in Nootdorp, an annual event where the proceeds go to charity. This year Quina Care was the winner. Many books and plants were sold during a sunny day with a proceeds to be proud of: € 2,400. Many thanks to all the volunteers who made this possible!! #nootdorp #nove #volunteers #quinacare" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DJg-EUdS1vK/)

[Besides medical volunteers there are also non-medi
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Besides medical volunteers there are also non-medical volunteers who put a lot of time and effort into the maintenance and improvement of Hospital San Miguel. They have taken on a wide range of tasks, from painting and maintaining air conditioning to repairing medical equipment. It is impressive to see how much work they have accomplished. It is partly thanks to the willpower of these volunteers that Hospital San Miguel functions at such a professional level. #voluntering #quinacare #hospitalsanmiguel #putumayo" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DJciOqwSTP_/)

[Dit zijn de laatste dagen van de Wilde Week van Wi
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Dit zijn de laatste dagen van de Wilde Week van Wilde Ganzen. Doneer nu zodat Wilde Ganzen het bedrag nog verdubbelt zodat wij betere en completere zorg kunnen leveren aan de mensen van Putumayo met een nieuw echoapparaat!" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DI4QonIMi9H/)

[Het is nog steeds de Wilde Week van Wilde Ganzen!
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Het is nog steeds de Wilde Week van Wilde Ganzen! Ziekenhuis San Miguel heeft dringend een nieuw echoapparaat nodig en daar willen we deze week aandacht voor vragen. Voor veel patiënten is een echo essentieel om een ​​diagnose te stellen. Maar ook voor zwangere vrouwen is een echo onmisbaar om de zwangerschap goed te kunnen monitoren. Doneer deze week en Wilde Ganzen verdubbelt uw donatie!" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DIy348NO0xC/)

[Today is the start of the Wild Week of Wilde Ganze
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Today is the start of the Wild Week of Wilde Ganzen! This week Wilde Ganzen is asking for extra attention for its projects and this is rewarded with a doubling of every donation that comes in. Quina Care has a project together with Wilde Ganzen for the financing of a new ultrasound machine. Let's try to get the purchase of this essential machine done this week! Find link in bio. #wildeganzen #wildeweek #quinacare #diagnostics #improvingruralhealth" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DIpLayBOKyb/)

[Surgical brigade un éxito! We have just completed
{% image src="/media/other/placeholder.png" caption="Surgical brigade un éxito! We have just completed two weeks of many surgeries. Almost forty patients received a surgical solution for problems they had been struggling with for years, mostly hernias. In addition, also a few acute surgeries. A big THANK YOU to the visiting surgeon Mart Bender and his wife Etje and Karin Martens, surgical assistent. And of course a big thank you to our fantastic team that worked day and night to make this possible and provide high-quality care. We look forward to the next brigade! #globalsurgery #quinacare #putumayo #lmic #improvingruralhealth" align="center" /%}](https://www.instagram.com/p/DIjUbLXOEW1/)

